&lt;p style=&quot;font-weight: normal;&quot;&gt;Welcome to our podcast series, &lt;em&gt;Coffee with the Council&lt;/em&gt;. I&apos;m Alicia Malone, Director of Communications and Public Relations for the PCI Security Standards Council. Well, it is hard to believe that we are already in February, but as we kick off 2026, we want to take a moment to also acknowledge all that the Council accomplished in 2025, including the recent release of the Council’s first-ever Annual Report. Joining me today to talk about this report and what we can expect in the year ahead is PCI SSC&apos;s Executive Director, Gina Gobeyn. Welcome, Gina!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://theshamblog.com/an-ai-agent-published-a-hit-piece-on-me/&quot;&gt;Interesting&lt;/a&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Summary: An AI agent of unknown ownership autonomously wrote and published a personalized hit piece about me after I rejected its code, attempting to damage my reputation and shame me into accepting its changes into a mainstream python library. This represents a first-of-its-kind case study of misaligned AI behavior in the wild, and raises serious concerns about currently deployed AI agents executing blackmail threats.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
